f(x)={{\left| 1-x \right|}^{-0.5}}\exp (-{{\left| 1-x \right|}^{0.5}})
x>0
u={{\left| 1-x \right|}^{0.5}}
du
u=\sqrt{|1-x|}
u=\begin{cases} \sqrt{1-x},&\text{if }x\le 1\\\\ \sqrt{x-1},&\text{if }x>1\;, \end{cases}\tag{1}
|1-x|=\begin{cases} 1-x,&\text{if }1-x\ge 0\\\\ -(1-x)=x-1,&\text{if }1-x<0\;. \end{cases}
du=\begin{cases} -\frac12(1-x)^{-1/2}dx,&\text{if }x<1\\\\ \frac12(x-1)^{-1/2}dx,&\text{if }x>1\;. \end{cases}\tag{2}
x<1
x>1
x\le 1
(1)
x<1
(2)
